 on a flight to Paris. Over the past two years, Juda has battled through injuries and mental fatigue.\n\nJuda is this year’s NCAA Floor exercise Champion, on of his favorites.\n\nSubscribe to ourNews 10 newsletterandYouTube pageto receive the latest local news and weather.Looking to hire people, or grow your business through advertising? Gray Digital Media is your one-stop marketing solution.Learnmore.\n\nCopyright 2024 WILX. All rights reserved.", "title": "University of Michigan gymnast Paul Juda to compete in 2024 Paris Olympics", "top-image": "https://gray-wilx-prod.gtv-cdn.com/resizer/v2/YGKRLL7NFFGSLBN4UEUF4XDWVY.jpg?auth=1ae6d7118c88fc46b57563b2c32acc884d258e8c089aad65ec74da0c297753cc&width=800&height=450&smart=true", "domain": "www.wilx.com", "lang": "en", "author": "", "description": "Team USA gymnast Paul Juda is a first-time Olympian. In an Instagram post, he said the experience “transcends explanation.”", "keywords": "local news,paul juda,olympics,paris,michigan,gymnastics,2024"}